    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six powerplant. This engine utilizes individual throttle bodies and a Double-VANOS variable valve timing system, both of which have been meticulously maintained to ensure a linear power band up to the 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a limited-slip differential, offering precise engagement and mechanical traction. The chassis has been addressed with rear subframe reinforcement to prevent floor-pan fatigue, a critical preventative measure for this platform. Suspension remains taut with upgraded bushings, preserving the original MacPherson strut and multi-link geometry for exceptional lateral stability. While the exterior shows minor road wear consistent with its 'good' condition, the vehicle is mechanically robust with no signs of rod bearing failure or cooling system fatigue. A purist-spec example optimized for tactile feedback and performance longevity.",
